## Proposed Changes

### Architecture Decision: Build vs Buy

Per CLAUDE.md "Build vs Buy" philosophy:
- **NOT using:** react-hook-form (too opinionated), survey.js (bloated), formik (complex)
- **Building:** Custom form builder with our own field registry
- **Reusing:** Our existing CustomFieldEditor component for field definitions
- **Total control:** 90% custom code, 10% utility libraries (uuid, date-fns if needed)

### Data Model

**Form Template:**
```typescript
interface FormTemplate {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  fields: FormField[];
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
  settings: {
    allowMultipleSubmissions: boolean;
    showSubmissionCount: boolean;
    resetPeriod?: 'daily' | 'weekly' | 'monthly' | 'never';
  };
}

interface FormField {
  id: string;
  type: 'text' | 'number' | 'date' | 'time' | 'select' | 'multiselect' | 'checkbox' | 'radio' | 'textarea' | 'rating' | 'scale';
  label: string;
  description?: string;
  required: boolean;
  options?: string[]; // For select/radio/multiselect
  validation?: {
    min?: number;
    max?: number;
    pattern?: string;
  };
  order: number;
}
```

**Form Response:**
```typescript
interface FormResponse {
  id: string;
  formId: string;
  answers: Record<string, any>; // field.id -> value
  submittedAt: Date;
}
```

